Preconditions:
The input array `nums` is not null.
The input array `nums` has at least two elements.
The input integer `k` is greater than or equal to The input integer `t` is greater than or equal to 
Postconditions:
The method returns `true` if there exist two distinct indices `i` and `j` in the array such that `abs(nums[i] - nums[j]) <= t` and `abs(i - j) <= k`.
The method returns `false` if there are no two distinct indices `i` and `j` in the array such that `abs(nums[i] - nums[j]) <= t` and `abs(i - j) <= k`.